{
  "texts": [
    "Intriguingly, two positions (6 and 8) produce slightly negative ∆P t, indicating that in isolation they introduce interference rather than denoising.",
    "In contrast, four positions: 1, 16, 21, and 23, stand out, each contributing ∆P t > 0.05.",
    "These peaks high-light the \"when\" of Head 6's causal intervention: specific segments of the input sequence are critical for steering the model back toward the correct classification.Importantly, summing these individual contributionsT -1 t=0 ∆P t ≈ 0.43underestimates the full-head effect (∆P full head ≈ 0.68).",
    "This discrepancy underscores that Head 6's overall influence is not simply additive across timesteps.",
    "Instead, it arises from nonlinear synergies enabled by self-attention, residual connections, and layer normalization, components that integrate information across positions."
  ]
}